{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Provide financial support to all workers who self-isolate due to Covid-19",
        "additional_details": "Many tax paying workers will be in severe financial hardship without help. It is not fair that additional support has only been made available to benefit claimants.\r\n\r\nMillions of workers who may be required to self-isolate have families to support and mortgages/rents to pay, and have been paying taxes while working. The least the Government can do is help them when they genuinely need it.\r\n\r\n\u00a3500 could be the difference between self-isolating or not, for some who don't have savings to fall back on.",
        "background": "I would like the Government to pay \u00a3500 to every worker that does not receive full pay whilst having to self-isolate, regardless of income. This should cover employees and the self-employed",
